en.question:
&lt;p&gt;In a certain code language,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#39;A + B&amp;#39; means &amp;#39;A is the daughter of B&amp;#39;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#39;A - B&amp;#39; means &amp;#39;A is the brother of B&amp;#39;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#39;A &amp;times; B&amp;#39; means &amp;#39;A is the wife of B&amp;#39; and&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;#39;A &amp;divide; B&amp;#39; means &amp;#39;A is the father of B&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &amp;#39;P + Q &amp;divide; R &amp;times; S - T&amp;#39;, then based on the above, how is P related to T?&lt;/p&gt;

