&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A alone can complete the task in 22 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A and B work on alternate days with B starting first&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The task is completed in 11.5 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total Work = Time &amp;times; Efficiency&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let total work = LCM of 22 = 22 units (for easy calculation)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Efficiency of A = 22 &amp;divide; 22 = 1 unit/day&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since A and B work alternately starting with B, in 11.5 days:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B works on Day: 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11 &amp;rarr; 6 full days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A works on Day: 2, 4, 6, 8, 10, and 0.5 of Day 12 &amp;rarr; 5.5 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A&amp;rsquo;s total work = 5.5 &amp;times; 1 = 5.5 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remaining work = 22 - 5.5 = 16.5 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This 16.5 units is done by B in 6 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; B&amp;rsquo;s efficiency = 16.5 &amp;divide; 6 = 2.75 units/day&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, we need to find the time taken by B alone to complete 3/4 of the original work:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3/4 of 22 = 16.5 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = 16.5 &amp;divide; 2.75 = 6 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; B alone will complete 3/4 of the work in 6 days.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Original volume of the cuboid = V&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Length is doubled = 2 &amp;times; original length&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Height is halved = 1/2 &amp;times; original height&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Breadth is tripled = 3 &amp;times; original breadth&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Volume of a cuboid = Length &amp;times; Breadth &amp;times; Height&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;New Volume = (2 &amp;times; original length) &amp;times; (3 &amp;times; original breadth) &amp;times; (1/2 &amp;times; original height)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Volume = 2 &amp;times; 3 &amp;times; 1/2 &amp;times; (original length &amp;times; original breadth &amp;times; original height)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Volume = (6/2) &amp;times; V&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Volume = 3V&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The volume of the cuboid after changes is 3V.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Length of Train 1 = 170 m&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Length of Train 2 = 480 m&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of Train 1 = 70 km/h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of Train 2 = 80 km/h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative Speed = Speed of Train 2 - Speed of Train 1 (as both trains are moving in the same direction)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time = Distance / Speed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Distance to be covered = Length of Train 1 + Length of Train 2 = 170 + 480 = 650 m&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative Speed = Speed of Train 2 - Speed of Train 1 = 80 - 70 = 10 km/h&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Convert relative speed to m/s:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative Speed = 10 &amp;times; (1000 / 3600) = 10 &amp;times; 5 / 18 = 50 / 18 m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time = Distance / Speed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = 650 / (50 / 18)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = 650 &amp;times; (18 / 50)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = (650 &amp;times; 18) / 50&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = 11700 / 50&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = 234 seconds&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Convert time to minutes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = 234 / 60 = 3.9 minutes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The time taken by the faster train to completely cross the slower train is 3.9 minutes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total amount Manoj has = ‚Çπ1612&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rate of interest (r) = 8% per annum&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time for Anand (t&lt;sub&gt;A&lt;/sub&gt;) = 13 years&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time for Anil (t&lt;sub&gt;An&lt;/sub&gt;) = 14 years&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Amount received by Anand after 13 years = Amount received by Anil after 14 years&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Amount (A) = Principal (P) &amp;times; (1 + )&lt;sup&gt;t&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the amount given to Anand be ‚Çπx.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then, the amount given to Anil is ‚Çπ(1612 - x).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Amount received by Anand after 13 years = x &amp;times; (1 + )&lt;sup&gt;13&lt;/sup&gt; = x &amp;times; (1.08)&lt;sup&gt;13&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Amount received by Anil after 14 years = (1612 - x) &amp;times; (1 + )&lt;sup&gt;14&lt;/sup&gt; = (1612 - x) &amp;times; (1.08)&lt;sup&gt;14&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the question:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;x &amp;times; (1.08)&lt;sup&gt;13&lt;/sup&gt; = (1612 - x) &amp;times; (1.08)&lt;sup&gt;14&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = (1612 - x) &amp;times; (1.08)&lt;sup&gt;14&lt;/sup&gt; / (1.08)&lt;sup&gt;13&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = (1612 - x) &amp;times; 1.08&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 1612 &amp;times; 1.08 - 1.08x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x + 1.08x = 1612 &amp;times; 1.08&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 2.08x = 1740.96&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;1740.96 /&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;2.08&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 837&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; Manoj gave ‚Çπ837 to Anand.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

