&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Distance between station A and station B = 370 km&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of train starting from A = 20 km/hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of train starting from B = 50 km/hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Train from A starts at 9:00 A.M.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Train from B starts at 10:00 A.M.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative speed (when moving towards each other) = Speed of train A + Speed of train B&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken to meet = Distance / Relative speed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative speed = 20 + 50 = 70 km/hr&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Distance covered by Train A from 9:00 A.M. to 10:00 A.M.:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Distance = Speed &amp;times; Time&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Distance = 20 &amp;times; 1 = 20 km&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remaining distance to cover = Total distance - Distance covered by Train A&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remaining distance = 370 - 20 = 350 km&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken to cover the remaining distance:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time = Distance / Relative speed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time = 350 / 70&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Time = 5 hours&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Meeting time = Start time of Train B + Time taken to meet&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Meeting time = 10:00 A.M. + 5 hours&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Meeting time = 3:00 P.M.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Answer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The trains meet at &lt;strong&gt;3:00 P.M.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Average weight of Anwar, Amit, and Gopal = 45 kg.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Average weight of Anwar and Amit = 43 kg.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Average weight of Amit and Gopal = 42 kg.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Average weight = Total weight / Number of people.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the weights of Anwar, Amit, and Gopal be A, M, and G, respectively.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total weight of Anwar, Amit, and Gopal = 45 &amp;times; 3 = 135&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total weight of Anwar and Amit = 43 &amp;times; 2 = 86&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total weight of Amit and Gopal = 42 &amp;times; 2 = 84&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From the above:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A + M + G = 135&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A + M = 86&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;M + G = 84&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Subtract A + M = 86 from A + M + G = 135:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; G = 135 - 86 = 49&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Subtract M + G = 84 from A + M + G = 135:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; A = 135 - 84 = 51&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To find M:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Substitute A = 51 in A + M = 86:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 51 + M = 86&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; M = 86 - 51 = 35&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The weight of Amit (M) is 35 kg.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; is the fourth proportional to (2/7), (7/12), 8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; is the fourth proportional to (5/6), (4/3), 10.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a, b, c are given, and d is the fourth proportional, then:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;d = (b &amp;times; c) / a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; : F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; / F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = 2/7, b = 7/12, c = 8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using the formula,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = (b &amp;times; c) / a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = ((7/12) &amp;times; 8) / (2/7)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = (56/12) &amp;divide; (2/7)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = (56/12) &amp;times; (7/2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = (56 &amp;times; 7) / (12 &amp;times; 2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = 392 / 24&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = 49 / 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = 5/6, b = 4/3, c = 10&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using the formula,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = (b &amp;times; c) / a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = ((4/3) &amp;times; 10) / (5/6)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = (40/3) &amp;divide; (5/6)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = (40/3) &amp;times; (6/5)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = (40 &amp;times; 6) / (3 &amp;times; 5)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = 240 / 15&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = 16&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now, F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; : F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; / F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; : F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = (49 / 3) &amp;divide; 16&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; : F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = (49 / 3) &amp;times; (1 / 16)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; : F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; = 49 / 48&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ratio F&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; : F&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; is 49 : 48.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

