&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total population = 369000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of males = 186000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of literate population = 45%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of literate males = 45%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of literate people = (Percentage of literate population / 100) &amp;times; Total population&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of literate males = (Percentage of literate males / 100) &amp;times; Number of males&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of literate females = Total number of literate people - Number of literate males&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of females = Total population - Number of males&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of literate females = (Number of literate females / Number of females) &amp;times; 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of literate people = (45 / 100) &amp;times; 369000 = 0.45 &amp;times; 369000 = 166050&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of literate males = (45 / 100) &amp;times; 186000 = 0.45 &amp;times; 186000 = 83700&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of literate females = 166050 - 83700 = 82350&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of females = 369000 - 186000 = 183000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of literate females = (82350 / 183000) &amp;times; 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of literate females &amp;asymp; 45%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Percentage of literate females = &amp;asymp; 45&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; Approximately 45% of females are literate.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Amit&amp;#39;s investment = ‚Çπ5400&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Gopal&amp;#39;s investment = ‚Çπ9400&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time = 6 years&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Difference in interest = ‚Çπ960&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simple Interest (SI) = (Principal &amp;times; Rate &amp;times; Time) / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the rate of interest be R%.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Interest for Amit = (5400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Interest for Gopal = (9400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Difference in interest = Interest for Gopal - Interest for Amit&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 = [(9400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100] - [(5400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 = [(9400 - 5400) &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6] / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 = [(4000 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 &amp;times; 100 = 4000 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 96000 = 24000 &amp;times; R&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; R = 96000 / 24000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; R = 4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The rate of interest per annum is 4%.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

