&lt;p&gt;‡§∏‡§Æ‡§Ø = 6 ‡§µ‡§∞‡•ç‡§∑&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ö‡§Ç‡§§‡§∞ = ‚Çπ960&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§Ø‡•Å‡§ï‡•ç‡§§ ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‡§∏‡§æ‡§ß‡§æ‡§∞‡§£ ‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú (SI) = (‡§Æ‡•Ç‡§≤‡§ß‡§® &amp;times; ‡§¶‡§∞ &amp;times; ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§Ø) / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‡§ó‡§£‡§®‡§æ:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‡§Æ‡§æ‡§®‡§æ, ‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú ‡§¶‡§∞ R% ‡§π‡•à‡•§&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‡§Ö‡§Æ‡§ø‡§§ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú = (5400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‡§ó‡•ã‡§™‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú = (9400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ö‡§Ç‡§§‡§∞ = ‡§ó‡•ã‡§™‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú - ‡§Ö‡§Æ‡§ø‡§§ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 = [(9400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100] - [(5400 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 = [(9400 - 5400) &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6] / 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 = [(4000 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6) / 100]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; ‚Çπ960 &amp;times; 100 = 4000 &amp;times; R &amp;times; 6&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 96000 = 24000 &amp;times; R&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; R = 96000 / 24000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; R = 4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§§‡§ø ‡§µ‡§∞‡•ç‡§∑ ‡§¨‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ú ‡§¶‡§∞ 4% ‡§π‡•à‡•§&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

en.text:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expression: [(44 &amp;divide; 4) &amp;times; {(48 &amp;divide; 8) + (21 &amp;divide; 5) &amp;times; (7 - 2)}]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Follow the BODMAS rule (Brackets, Orders, Division/Multiplication, Addition/Subtraction).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[(44 &amp;divide; 4) &amp;times; {(48 &amp;divide; 8) + (21 &amp;divide; 5) &amp;times; (7 - 2)}]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[11 &amp;times; {6&amp;nbsp;+ 21/5 &amp;times; 5}]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[11 &amp;times; {6&amp;nbsp;+ 21&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;}]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[11 &amp;times; 27]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;297&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the value of [(44 &amp;divide; 4) &amp;times; {(48 &amp;divide; 8) + (21 &amp;divide; 5) &amp;times; (7 - 2)}] is 297.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

hn.text:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‡§¶‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§π‡•à:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‡§µ‡•ç‡§Ø‡§Ç‡§ú‡§ï: [(44 &amp;divide; 4) x {(48 &amp;divide; 8) + (21 &amp;divide; 5) x (7 - 2)}]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§Ø‡•Å‡§ï‡•ç‡§§ ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BODMAS ‡§®‡§ø‡§Ø‡§Æ ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§™‡§æ‡§≤‡§® ‡§ï‡§∞‡•á‡§Ç (‡§ï‡•ã‡§∑‡•ç‡§†‡§ï, ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§Æ, ‡§≠‡§æ‡§ó/‡§ó‡•Å‡§£‡§æ, ‡§ú‡•ã‡§°‡§º/‡§ò‡§ü‡§æ‡§µ)‡•§&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‡§ó‡§£‡§®‡§æ:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[(44 &amp;divide; 4) x {(48 &amp;divide; 8) + (21 &amp;divide; 5) x (7 - 2)}]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[11 x {6 + 21/5 x 5}]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[11 x {6 + 21&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;}]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;[11 x 27]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;297&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‡§Ö‡§§‡§É [(44 &amp;divide; 4) x {(48 &amp;divide; 8) + (21 &amp;divide; 5) x (7 - 2)}] ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§® 297 ‡§π‡•à‡•§&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

en.text:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The price of a shirt is increased by 15%, decreased by 12%, and then increased by 8%.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Net percentage change = (Final Price - Initial Price) / Initial Price &amp;times; 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Final Price = Initial Price &amp;times; (1 + Percentage Change&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt;) &amp;times; (1 + Percentage Change&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;) &amp;times; (1 + Percentage Change&lt;sub&gt;3&lt;/sub&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the initial price of the shirt be 100.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After a 15% increase:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Price = 100 &amp;times; (1 + 15/100)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Price = 100 &amp;times; 1.15&amp;nbsp;= 115&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After a 12% decrease:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Price = 115 &amp;times; (1 - 12/100)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Price = 115 &amp;times; 0.88&amp;nbsp;= 101.2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After an 8% increase:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Price = 101.2 &amp;times; (1 + 8/100)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New Price = 101.2 &amp;times; 1.08&amp;nbsp;= 109.296&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Net percentage change:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Net Change = (Final Price - Initial Price) / Initial Price &amp;times; 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Net Change = (109.296 - 100) / 100 &amp;times; 100&amp;nbsp;= 9.296%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The net increase in the price of the shirt is approximately 9.3%.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 3&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Apportion&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to allocate or distribute something among individuals or groups. (‡§µ‡§ø‡§≠‡§æ‡§ú‡§ø‡§§ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡§æ)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The manager decided to &lt;strong&gt;apportion &lt;/strong&gt;the budget equally among all departments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Allocate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to assigning or distributing resources or responsibilities for a specific purpose. (‡§Ü‡§µ‡§Ç‡§ü‡§ø‡§§ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡§æ)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The government &lt;strong&gt;allocated &lt;/strong&gt;funds for building schools in rural areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the word &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Apportion&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is best defined by &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Allocate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To complicate&lt;/strong&gt; (‡§ú‡§ü‡§ø‡§≤ ‡§¨‡§®‡§æ‡§®‡§æ): To make something more difficult or complex.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Adding unnecessary details will only &lt;strong&gt;complicate &lt;/strong&gt;the problem.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To confess&lt;/strong&gt; (‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡•Ä‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡§æ): To admit or acknowledge something, often a wrongdoing.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He &lt;strong&gt;confessed &lt;/strong&gt;to his teacher that he had forgotten to do his homework.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To request&lt;/strong&gt; (‡§®‡§ø‡§µ‡•á‡§¶‡§® ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡§æ): To ask for something formally or politely.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She &lt;strong&gt;requested &lt;/strong&gt;a day off to attend her friend&amp;#39;s wedding.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The adverb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;barely&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;modifies the verb &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;make out&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;, describing the difficulty with which the action is performed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Barely&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;should generally appear before the verb when it modifies the action (verb).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In Option 2, the placement of &amp;#39;barely&amp;#39; after &amp;#39;make out&amp;#39; is incorrect and disrupts the meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct placement would be &amp;quot;Mohan could barely make out the distant figure.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 1: The usage of &amp;#39;barely&amp;#39; is correct, as it modifies &amp;#39;make out&amp;#39; and is placed before the verb.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 3: The adverb &amp;#39;often&amp;#39; is correctly placed before &amp;#39;make out&amp;#39; to describe frequency.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Option 4: The adverb &amp;#39;usually&amp;#39; is correctly placed before &amp;#39;make out&amp;#39; to describe frequency.&lt;/li&gt;
