&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;quot;neither&amp;quot; is a singular pronoun and must be followed by a singular verb. Therefore, &amp;quot;has&amp;quot; should replace &amp;quot;have&amp;quot; in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct construction is &amp;quot;neither has any papers,&amp;quot; ensuring subject-verb agreement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;This rule ensures grammatical correctness and clarity in the sentence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

